  "wikitext": "\n'''2-1-240\n\nRefractive Index (of a medium)\n\nRatio of the velocity of light in vacuum to the velocity of light in the medium.\n\nSymbol: n\n\n\nNote: This index is equal to the ratio of the sines of the angles of incidence (?1) and refraction (?2) when a ray crosses the surface separating vacuum and medium.\n\nReference: C.I.E. (modified)\n\n{{IALAFooter}}\n\n{{languages|Refractive Index}}\n[[Category:2.1 Optics and Vision]]\n[[Category:Alphabetical Index]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 1970-89 Edition]]"
